ds/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23267893/jbareham_220224_ecl1072_pokemon_0001.jpeg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23267893/jbareham_220224_ecl1072_pokemon_0001.jpeg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23267893/jbareham_220224_ecl1072_pokemon_0001.jpeg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23267893/jbareham_220224_ecl1072_pokemon_0001.jpeg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23267893/jbareham_220224_ecl1072_pokemon_0001.jpeg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23267893/jbareham_220224_ecl1072_pokemon_0001.jpeg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: James Bareham/Polygon | Source image: The Pokémon Company\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Michael McWhertor\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"36\" height=\"36\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/Michael-McWhertor-Green-Purple-1.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=48 1x, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/Michael-McWhertor-Green-Purple-1.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=96 2x\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/Michael-McWhertor-Green-Purple-1.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=96\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/authors/michael-mcwhertor\"\u003eMichael McWhertor\u003c/a\u003e \u003cspan\u003eis a journalist with more than 17 years of experience covering video games, technology, movies, TV, and entertainment.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Pokémon Company has a Pokémon Presents showcase planned for July, promising viewers “the latest updates and news from the world of Pokémon.” It’s the second of these events in 2025 so far, \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/530790/pokemon-presents-2025-news-announcements-all-recap\"\u003efollowing February’s Pokémon Day event\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe latest Pokémon Presents showcase will stream on \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCFctpiB_Hnlk3ejWfHqSm6Q\"\u003ethe official Pokémon YouTube channel\u003c/a\u003e on Tuesday, July 22, starting at 9 a.m. EDT/6 a.m. PDT. The Pokémon Company hasn’t yet said how long this Pokémon Presents event will be.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAnd while The Pokémon Company hasn’t said what games will be discussed, we can probably expect an update on \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon/530077/pokemon-legends-z-a-trailer-announcement\"\u003ePokémon Legends: Z-A\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e, which is coming to Nintendo Switch (and Nintendo Switch 2) \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gaming/601945/pokemon-legends-z-a-finally-receives-release-date-with-a-new-pokemon-presents-revealed\"\u003eon Oct. 16\u003c/a\u003e. That game will feature a new adventure set in Lumiose City in the franchise’s Kalos region, introduced in \u003cem\u003ePokémon X\u003c/em\u003e and \u003cem\u003ePokémon Y\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn February, The Pokémon Company announced a new game, \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/530598/pokemon-champions-battle-game-announced\"\u003ePokémon Champions\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e, so hopefully we’ll get more details on that upcoming project. We can also expect updates on many of the ongoing live-service games featuring Pokémon, including \u003cem\u003ePokémon Trading Card Game Pocket\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003ePokémon Go\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003ePokémon Unite\u003c/em\u003e, and \u003cem\u003ePokémon Sleep\u003c/em\u003e. Beyond games, a second season of \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24009728/pokemon-concierge-netflix-animation-review-new-show\"\u003ePokémon Concierge\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e is \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/tv/530776/pokemon-concierge-season-2-netflix-release-date\"\u003ecoming to Netflix in September\u003c/a\u003e, and the company has \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon/23623837/pokemon-detective-pikachu-2-director-writer-release\"\u003ea follow-up\u003c/a\u003e to 2019’s movie \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2019/5/2/18527380/detective-pikachu-review-pokemon\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ePokémon: Detective Pikachu\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e in development.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eNo doubt The Pokémon Company will have a few surprises in store as well. After all, we’re approaching the third anniversary of the most recent mainline games in the franchise, \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/23462736/pokemon-scarlet-and-violet-review-release-date-nintendo-switch\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ePokémon Scarlet\u003c/em\u003e and \u003cem\u003eViolet\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eSee More:\u003cspan\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gaming\"\u003eGaming\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003